---
import BaseLayout from "../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
---

<BaseLayout title="Colophon" description="How noahairmet.com was designed, built, and reviewed.">
  <header class="page-hero">
    <p class="indexed-label"><span>C</span> Colophon</p>
    <h1>The site should practice the accountability it talks about.</h1>
    <p>This page records how the site was built, where AI contributed, and which decisions remain Noah’s responsibility.</p>
  </header>

  <div class="page-content">
    <section class="prose-grid">
      <h2>Design</h2>
      <div class="prose">
        <p>The visual system draws from civic modernism and editorial publishing: strong type, visible structure, restrained color, and real artifacts rather than generic technology imagery.</p>
        <p>The first design pass explored portrait-led editorial, dark operational, and bright civic directions. The final system selected the brighter direction because it was distinctive without making governance feel secretive, militarized, or like an AI startup.</p>
      </div>
    </section>
    <section class="prose-grid">
      <h2>AI assistance</h2>
      <div class="prose">
        <p>OpenAI Codex agents assisted with repository auditing, architecture comparison, content structure, visual exploration, implementation, and testing under Noah’s direction.</p>
        <p>Noah set the goals, rejected directions that felt wrong, defined the boundary between religious projects and professional identity, and remains responsible for the claims published here. AI assistance is disclosed because authorship includes judgment—not only keystrokes.</p>
      </div>
    </section>
    <section class="prose-grid">
      <h2>Technology</h2>
      <div class="prose">
        <p>Astro generates static HTML. TypeScript validates the content model. CSS is handwritten. The fonts are self-hosted. Cloudflare Workers Static Assets serves the build without a home-server origin or application runtime.</p>
        <p>The site uses no UI framework, analytics, database, authentication, client-side application shell, or third-party font request.</p>
      </div>
    </section>
    <section class="prose-grid">
      <h2>Review standard</h2>
      <div class="prose">
        <p>Build, type, link, responsive, and accessibility checks are part of the release process. Material professional claims should be checked against the résumé or source project before publication.</p>
        <p>Last substantive review: July 2026.</p>
      </div>
    </section>
  </div>
</BaseLayout>
